name: visitDeleteCommand
javadoc:
/**
 * Adds a delete command to be executed on the specified object.
 *
 * @param object The object that will be deleted.
 */
improved_javadoc:
/**
 * Adds a delete command to be executed on the specified object. This operation does not modify the collection's state, 
 * but rather schedules the deletion of the object in the pending deletions queue.
 *
 * @param object The object that will be deleted. It must not be null.
 */

name: visitInsertCommand
javadoc:
/**
 * Adds an insertion command to be executed on the database.
 *
 * @param object The object that will be inserted into the database.
 */
improved_javadoc:
/**
 * Adds an insertion command to be executed on the database, incrementing its count if it already exists in the collection.
 *
 * @param object The object that will be inserted into the database. It must not be null.
 * @throws NullPointerException if the object is null
 */

name: visitKeepCommand
javadoc:
/**
 * Visits a keep command.
 *
 * If there are no pending deletions or insertions, increments the number of skipped commands.
 * Otherwise, handles the replacement and resets the pending collections.
 *
 * @param object the object to visit (not used in this implementation)
 */
improved_javadoc:
/**
 * Visits a keep command.
 *
 * If there are no pending deletions or insertions, increments the number of skipped commands.
 * Otherwise, handles the replacement and resets the pending collections.
 *
 * @param object the object to visit (not used in this implementation)
 * @return none
 * @throws none
 */
